Sentencas: The perovskite material Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta was used as an anode in direct propane fueled solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Co-generation of electricity and chemicals from propane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells with anode containing nano-bimetallic catalyst

Sentencas: After exposure of the initial single phase Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta to a reducing atmosphere at 900 degrees C, it transformed to a two-phase system with nano-particles of a Co-Fe bimetallic alloy uniformly distributed on a Ruddlesden-Popper ceramic phase.
Titulo: Co-generation of electricity and chemicals from propane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells with anode containing nano-bimetallic catalyst

Sentencas: High cell power output and good stability were obtained using propane as the fuel and ambient air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Co-generation of electricity and chemicals from propane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells with anode containing nano-bimetallic catalyst

Sentencas: Due to the catalytic effect of the Co-Fe bimetallic alloy in the SOFC operating conditions, macromolecular compounds of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (PAHs) were generated as by-products in the exhaust stream of the anode.
Titulo: Co-generation of electricity and chemicals from propane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells with anode containing nano-bimetallic catalyst

Sentencas: This novel anode system successfully demonstrated the co-generation of electricity and high value end use chemicals from direct hydrocarbon fueled SOFC systems.
Titulo: Co-generation of electricity and chemicals from propane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells with anode containing nano-bimetallic catalyst
